            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ENVDA is a piece of software known as a screen reader. A screen reader does exactly what the name suggests: it reads out what is on the screen using synthesized speech. On Windows, there are three pieces of screen reader software that blind or low vision users will typically use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJob Access With Speech (JAWS) from Freedom Scientific.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENon-Visual Desktop Access (NVDA) a free, open-source screen reader from NVAccess.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMicrosoft Narrator from Microsoft, built into the Windows operating system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis guide is about NVDA. NVDA is one of the most popular pieces of screen reader software and follows the WCAG more strictly than JAWS, so when you come across a WCAG violation, you will more easily notice it. JAWS, on the other hand, tries to smooth over the experience on poorly conforming or non-compliant pages using various methods, so WCAG violations might not be communicated clearly or at all.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "a8790ec0-2c08-4153-8546-9c5ef4763691",
      "key": "ebf7f5c6-f5e8-4e31-a20f-d05ff3d57aa3",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "headerText",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How to install NVDA"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerTextColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "label": "black",
            "value": "#000000"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerAccentColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "{\r\n  \u0022label\u0022: \u0022secondary-medium\u0022,\r\n  \u0022value\u0022: \u0022#FFC44D\u0022\r\n}"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerMarginBottom",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b87dee17-4242-4d83-9f36-63aae1204d93",
      "key": "032d07a7-ff3a-4274-b3cf-80725c37cc25",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "content",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ETo install NVDA, you first need to \u003Ca target=\u0022_blank\u0022 data-router-slot=\u0022disabled\u0022 href=\u0022https://www.nvaccess.org/download/\u0022 title=\u0022www.nvaccess.org\u0022 type=\u0022external\u0022\u003Edownload the NVDA installer\u003C/a\u003E. After you have downloaded the installer, double-click it. Go through the steps presented to you in the installer. At some point you will be asked to confirm administrator privileges. Once you have gone through all the steps in the installer, you will have NVDA installed.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "a8790ec0-2c08-4153-8546-9c5ef4763691",
      "key": "5416a69c-33c3-4678-96e2-eba2df3d658d",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "headerText",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "The NVDA key"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerTextColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "label": "black",
            "value": "#000000"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerAccentColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "{\r\n  \u0022label\u0022: \u0022secondary-medium\u0022,\r\n  \u0022value\u0022: \u0022#FFC44D\u0022\r\n}"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerMarginBottom",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b87dee17-4242-4d83-9f36-63aae1204d93",
      "key": "a33d28ab-f64f-4c74-8279-8470717c9f13",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "content",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EFor some keyboard commands in NVDA, you have to press what\u2019s called the NVDA Key. By default, it is set to the Insert key, but you can change that in the NVDA settings located in the system tray.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "a8790ec0-2c08-4153-8546-9c5ef4763691",
      "key": "977d1177-f8cd-44e2-910b-ea6d480f5f0d",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "headerText",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Starting and restarting NVDA"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerTextColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "label": "black",
            "value": "#000000"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerAccentColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "{\r\n  \u0022label\u0022: \u0022secondary-medium\u0022,\r\n  \u0022value\u0022: \u0022#FFC44D\u0022\r\n}"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerMarginBottom",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b87dee17-4242-4d83-9f36-63aae1204d93",
      "key": "b1298397-fcf9-4c2a-a225-fd1a181ed368",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "content",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EYou can start or restart NVDA using two different methods:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOpen the Start menu, type \u201CNVDA\u201D and hit Enter\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPress the key combination Control\u002B Alt\u002B N\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "a8790ec0-2c08-4153-8546-9c5ef4763691",
      "key": "78f5a77c-33e0-465b-97bf-4d4fadf2f9de",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "headerText",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Changing the NVDA voice and other settings"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerTextColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "label": "black",
            "value": "#000000"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerAccentColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "{\r\n  \u0022label\u0022: \u0022secondary-medium\u0022,\r\n  \u0022value\u0022: \u0022#FFC44D\u0022\r\n}"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerMarginBottom",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b87dee17-4242-4d83-9f36-63aae1204d93",
      "key": "13c7662b-e9d3-4df5-9c40-cdb290c6d89e",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "content",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EYou can change the voice that NVDA uses and a number of other settings in the NVDA settings menu, which can be accessed through the system tray.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFor commands to navigate using NVDA, refer to the \u003Ca target=\u0022\u0022 data-router-slot=\u0022disabled\u0022 href=\u0022/{localLink:c776cb6d-bf4e-4fcf-ad99-2212fa8a8a4a}\u0022 title=\u0022Narrator Keyboard Commands\u0022 type=\u0022document\u0022\u003ENVDA keyboard commands\u003C/a\u003E reference.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "a8790ec0-2c08-4153-8546-9c5ef4763691",
      "key": "47995055-5325-4fb8-bdd5-5306d1d9dcca",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "headerText",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Screen Curtain"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerTextColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "label": "black",
            "value": "#000000"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerAccentColor",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "{\r\n  \u0022label\u0022: \u0022secondary-medium\u0022,\r\n  \u0022value\u0022: \u0022#FFC44D\u0022\r\n}"
        },
        {
          "alias": "headerMarginBottom",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": null
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b87dee17-4242-4d83-9f36-63aae1204d93",
      "key": "212870f0-b578-418d-991f-43006c77de8d",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "content",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ENVDA, like other screen readers, has a useful feature that can be used for testing called screen curtain. The screen curtain blacks out your entire screen without the need to turn off your monitor. Unlike Narrator, NVDA does not have a keyboard shortcut to enable and disable this feature at this time. As a result, you must be more familiar with navigating your computer non-visually to disable the feature once enabled.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
